Odaily Planet Daily News According to Lookonchain monitoring, whales are selling SOL, including: 
Address "4W1Ree" unstaked 159,028 SOL (US$16.5 million) at a price of US$102 4 hours ago, and sold 60,000 SOL (US$6.13 million); 
Address "5cPair" sold 89,734 SOL (US$9.67 million) at a price of US$108 14 hours ago

1. Bitcoin spot ETF had a total net outflow of 326 million US dollars yesterday, and continued to have net outflow for 4 days;
2. Bitwise CEO: BTC is an ideal value storage tool for the country to get rid of its dependence on the US dollar;
3. The giant whale received a 43,000 US dollar ETHFI airdrop, but accumulated a loss of about 11.9 million US dollars due to staking ETH;
4. Aave's "buyback proposal" has been passed, and it will start to buy back 1 million US dollars of AAVE every week tomorrow;
5. Strategy warns that when the market value of Bitcoin falls sharply or affects the ability to perform, it may be necessary to sell BTC to repay debts;
6. It is suspected that WLFI sold ETH to stop losses, and the floating loss has exceeded 125 million US dollars;
7. Arthur Hayes: With the reduction of US dollar export revenue, the market can no longer support US bonds and US stocks;
8. Ethereum spot ETF had a total net outflow of 3.2947 million US dollars yesterday, and none of the nine ETFs had a net inflow;
9. Binance will resume FUN U The settlement frequency of the perpetual contract funding rate is once every four hours;
10. The yield on the US 10-year Treasury bond rose to a nearly six-week high.
